      <span class="text-sm font-semibold text-emerald-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Website Builders</span>
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-4 mb-6">How to Convert a Webflow Site into a Mobile App</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-slate-600 mb-8">Our platform enables you to convert your existing Webflow design into native iOS and Android apps without the need for extensive redevelopment, maintaining your site's features and aesthetics while enhancing user engagement through push notifications and a superior mobile experience.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 px-4 bg-slate-50">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose prose-lg prose-slate">
      <p id>Webflow is growing fast as one of the world's most popular content management systems.</p><p id>It's rising particularly for eCommerce stores, with nearly <a href="https://trends.builtwith.com/shop/Webflow-Ecommerce" id>100,000 online stores worldwide</a> powered by&nbsp;Webflow.</p><p id>All these stores should have their own mobile app.&nbsp;But that raises the question... how to <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/how-to-create-an-app">build a mobile app</a> with Webflow?</p><p id>Luckily, there's an easy way to convert your Webflow website into a mobile app, without a huge investment or a ton of development work.</p><p id>So if you're interested in turning your successful Webflow site into iOS and Android apps, keep reading and learn how to do it.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-video w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="padding-bottom:56.206088992974244%" data-rt-type="video" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width data-rt-max-height="56.206088992974244%" data-rt-dimensions="854:480" data-page-url="https://youtu.be/O77GXQwwX_A?si=C2eRC2vCpU6TxvWt"><div id><iframe allowfullscreen="true" frameborder="0" scrolling="no" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/O77GXQwwX_A"></iframe></div></figure><h2 id>Can&nbsp;You Create Mobile Apps with Webflow?</h2><p id>Webflow is great for building unique, responsive web experiences in a short time.</p><p id>But, for now, it's only for the web. You're not able to use their intuitive platform to create mobile apps.</p><p id>And if you've got a successful website running on&nbsp;Webflow, it's not as easy as it would seem to just turn your website into a mobile app.</p><p id>If you go with a custom job, you'll need to build the framework of your mobile apps from scratch, then create a custom&nbsp;API to share data between your mobile apps and Webflow site.</p><p id>This is all going to cost a lot - and it's unsure whether it will be worth it.</p><p id>You're looking at a six figure+ cost, which will take a long time to pay off.</p><p id>If you're running an eCommerce store on Webflow, it absolutely makes sense to launch an app, as your own branded app could generate <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/ecom-app-revenue-calculator" id>tens of thousands in new revenue</a> per month for your store.</p><p id>But custom-building mobile apps will be a massive project, a lot of risk, and even if things go well, it will be a while before you see a positive ROI.</p><p id>However, if you use a service specially designed for <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/convert-website-to-mobile-app" id>turning a website into an app</a>, you could create a mobile app with Webflow much quicker, much cheaper, and with exponentially less risk.</p><h2 id>How to Convert Your Webflow Site Into an App&nbsp;(<em id>Without </em>a Six-Figure Cost)</h2><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a> is the easiest, and also most effective way to turn a Webflow site into a mobile app.</p><p id>MobiLoud is a service to convert websites into mobile apps.</p><p id>It works with all web technologies, platforms and site builders - and it'll work perfectly for your Webflow site.</p><p id>You'll be able to build a full-featured mobile app, with a native look and feel, while reusing everything from your Webflow website.</p><figure id class="w-richtext-figure-type-image w-richtext-align-fullwidth" style="max-width:2240px" data-rt-type="image" data-rt-align="fullwidth" data-rt-max-width="2240px"><div id><img src="https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/63894f0e251e567f6e443bfa/698ee626453b872ad57ce8b6_6865a4f352326f55503677f1_20250702T0915-c2436afb-af62-4680-adc3-802e5704fff4.webp" loading="lazy" alt="__wf_reserved_inherit" width="auto" height="auto" id></div><figcaption id>Some of the apps built with&nbsp;MobiLoud</figcaption></figure><p id>We do all the work for you, building the native mobile framework and UI for your app, and integrating your web content within the app.</p><p id>The result will be your web experience, upgraded for mobile, while still being managed from your Webflow backend.<br></p><p id>You don't need to worry about managing multiple platforms - just manage your website, as you normally would, and your apps will always stay in sync.</p><p id>It's a reasonable <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/pricing" id>cost</a>&nbsp;(a fraction of the cost of hiring developers, plus keeping developers on staff for updates and maintenance), and requires basically no overhead to manage.</p><p id>Your apps will have everything they need to look and feel just like million-dollar mobile apps, including <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/push-notifications-for-ecommerce" id>push notifications</a>, built in and working from day one.</p><p id>We've helped <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/case-studies" id>more than 2,000 businesses</a> launch their own apps, and save the cost and complexity of custom app development, while seamlessly turning their website into a native mobile experience that converts.</p><blockquote id>Want to learn more about how the process works?&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Get a free consultation</a> and get all your questions answered by our team of experts.</blockquote><h2 id>Webflow to App in Five Steps</h2><p id>If you want to keep what already works on your Webflow site, keep your same workflow, and launch an app that adds five figures in monthly revenue (without a huge investment, or massive overhead), try <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a>.</p><p id>The process is easy. As we're a fully managed service, there's basically nothing for you to do.&nbsp;You just sit back and wait for your apps to go live.</p><p id>Here's the five-step process that will take you from zero to having your own apps, live in the app stores.</p><h3 id>Step One: Kickoff Call</h3><p id>Start with a <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>consultation call</a>. We'll walk you through the process, show you examples of apps like yours we've built, and show you just what MobiLoud can do for you.</p><p id>You can get all your questions answered before you start, and share with our team any special requirements for your app.</p><h3 id>Step Two: Choose a Plan</h3><p id>When you're ready to move ahead, choose the <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/pricing" id>plan</a> that suits your needs.</p><p id>All plans come with unlimited push notifications, done-for-you app configuration, full white-labeling, and start from just a few hundred per month with no long-term commitments or contracts - so there's no risk.</p><h3 id>Step Three:&nbsp;Hand Over to Our Team</h3><p id>Just hand off the project to our team and we'll start building.</p><p id>As long as your Webflow site is fast, user-friendly and responsive on mobile, our team will have no trouble turning it into high-quality mobile apps.</p><p id>We do all the work to write native code that turns your site into legitimate mobile apps. All you need to do is wait.</p><h3 id>Step Four: Testing</h3><p id>Your app will be ready for testing in approximately two weeks.</p><p id>Try out the apps on your own devices, play around, and send us any feedback.</p><p id>We'll work off your feedback and fix any issues, before compiling a version of your app ready for launch.</p><h3 id>Step Five: Launch</h3><p id>Within a month, you'll be ready to go live.</p><p id>Our team handles the app store submission process for you, ensuring your app store listings go live without a hitch.</p><p id>Outside of this, you can start promoting your mobile apps on your website, to your email list and on any other active channels, and start building momentum with your first app users.</p><blockquote id>Ready to explore the process of turning your Webflow site into a mobile app? <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>Get a free consultation now</a> and talk it over with our team of experts.</blockquote><h2 id>Why Convert Your Webflow Web App into a Mobile App?</h2><p id>Is it really worth the hassle to build a mobile app for your Webflow site?</p><p id>After all, your website works great on mobile already. It's fast, responsive, and people can access it through mobile browsers.</p><p id>But there is still a lot of benefit to turning your Webflow site into a proper mobile app.</p><p id>First, there is basically no hassle.</p><p id><a href="https://www.mobiloud.com" id>MobiLoud</a> makes it easy. There's nothing for you to do, and we'll ship a native-feeling app that reuses your web code, and requires virtually no extra work to maintain.</p><p id>Second, you can drive more revenue from your current users, increase retention, and gain a direct line to your customers by launching an app.</p><p id>The <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/what-percentage-of-internet-traffic-is-mobile" id>mobile web's market</a> share continues to grow, and with it, your share of potential app users.</p><p id>Anyone who would visit your site more than once (your most valuable users) would almost certainly download your app, to make the experience easier.</p><p id>And people in apps convert at a higher rate, spend more in each transaction, and are more likely to return than mobile web users.</p><p id>Once you get people to download your apps, you can market to them with push notifications - a high-visibility channel that's basically free.</p><p id>Most important, an app gives you ownership and a direct line to your audience, which is extremely valuable today with other acquisition channels becoming more expensive or less reliable.</p><p id>So while your mobile site may work well, it's not going to compare to the benefits of having your own app.</p><h2 id>Ready to Convert Your Webflow Site into a Mobile App?</h2><p id>We’ve covered the main benefits of converting a Webflow site into a mobile app, why Webflow is not equipped to let you build an app directly, and why&nbsp;<a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/" id>MobiLoud</a> is the best way to do it.</p><p id>We also put forward a case for why <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/blog/canvas-is-enough" id>MobiLoud is the best option</a>.&nbsp;</p><p id>MobiLoud let’s you keep building the no code way, combining the best of Webflow with the best of mobile app UX. </p><p id>Success is all but guaranteed, and our development team are only ever an email or a Zoom call away to help out.&nbsp;</p><p id>With Webflow and MobiLoud, you can build a whole multichannel product using 100% no code tools, and launch an app for your site without having to go through the hassle of migrating your website to another platform, or building custom apps that don't sync with your site.</p><p id>To learn more, or to start the process, get in touch with us now and <a href="https://www.mobiloud.com/demo" id>schedule a free consultation</a>.</p><p id>We'll answer all your questions and explain, in-depth, how we'll bring your mobile apps to life.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

